{"id": "EUVD-2025-15926", "enisaUuid": "8cd5b040-4547-3981-89e7-1e03efed994d", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nptp: ocp: Fix NULL dereference in Adva board SMA sysfs operations\n\nOn Adva boards, SMA sysfs store/get operations can call\n__handle_signal_outputs() or __handle_signal_inputs() while the `irig`\nand `dcf` pointers are uninitialized, leading to a NULL pointer\ndereference in __handle_signal() and causing a kernel crash. Adva boards\ndon't use `irig` or `dcf` functionality, so add Adva-specific callbacks\n`ptp_ocp_sma_adva_set_outputs()` and `ptp_ocp_sma_adva_set_inputs()` that\navoid invoking `irig` or `dcf` input/output routines.", "datePublished": "2025-05-20T18:30:54", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-17T15:30:31", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-37910", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/5b349f9cdb4a9daa133bea267dfc0c383628387a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8a543d825e78b8d680d8f891381b83fbffdb0bb6", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e98386d79a23c57cf179fe4138322e277aa3aa74"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-37910", "GHSA-wfcc-qm3q-frp3"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.01, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0cf48183-ad52-39c8-8e26-1455e33bed20", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.14.6"}, {"id": "27d62beb-be3f-3d8e-a3cc-0f6f0206ef06", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "698bd7cd-2bf1-340d-92c2-aa37f0dcba6f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.28"}, {"id": "910a2b56-0f8a-350c-81d3-71be6198a69b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.15"}, {"id": "a21d0344-3852-34d7-b7c6-d9eaab6d31c7", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "ef61f5528fca6c3bbb2f8bc002fd1949c9d1f9b9 <e98386d79a23c57cf179fe4138322e277aa3aa74"}, {"id": "b8920eb9-a411-34da-aefb-cacfd8054365", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.9"}, {"id": "baa6d669-0277-3d3f-8277-56fd35fabe15", "product":